    "With the small sample size (n=4), therapists reviewed the questionnaire results individually.",
    "During the study, two subjects improved from moderate-to-severe anxiety and depression to mild levels, initially facing difficulties in functioning but eventually reporting none.",
    "One subject progressed from mild to minimal anxiety and depression and reported no functional difficulties.",
    "The remaining participant exhibited fluctuating symptoms, ranging from mild to minimal, initially facing some difficulties in functioning, but reporting none by the study's end.",
    "The findings of this study indicate that CaiTI was effective in reducing the severity of anxiety and depression, as well as enhancing daily functioning.8.3 Qualitative Evaluation from the Subjects and Therapists 8.3.1 Experiences and Feedback from Subjects."
